    <item>
      <title>Forward and inverse serach in Okular with NeoVim and Lazy plugin loader</title>
      <link>https://vaclavblazej.github.io/post/2023/synctex/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 26 May 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://vaclavblazej.github.io/post/2023/synctex/</guid>
      <description>&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;TLDR;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;pip3 install neovim-remote&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/vaclavblazej/nvim/blob/main/lua/blazeva1/lazy.lua&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;setup vimtex in lazy&lt;span style=&#34;white-space: nowrap;&#34;&gt;&amp;thinsp;↗&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/vaclavblazej/nvim/blob/main/after/plugin/vimtex.lua&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;configure vimtex&lt;span style=&#34;white-space: nowrap;&#34;&gt;&amp;thinsp;↗&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;set &amp;ldquo;&lt;code&gt;Okular/Settings/Configure Okular/Editor/Custom Text Editor&lt;/code&gt;&amp;rdquo; to &lt;code&gt;nvr --remote-silent +%l %f&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://vaclavblazej.github.io/post/2022/synctex/&#34;&gt;10 months ago&lt;/a&gt; I setup my vim to support jump to and from PDF viewer.&#xA;Since then I &lt;a href=&#34;https://vaclavblazej.github.io/post/2023/neovim/&#34;&gt;jumped into NeoVim&lt;/a&gt; which broke this setup, so here is the new one.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In NeoVim &lt;code&gt;~/.config/nvim/init.lua&lt;/code&gt; apart from the &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/folke/lazy.nvim&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;typical lazy setup&lt;span style=&#34;white-space: nowrap;&#34;&gt;&amp;thinsp;↗&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; we include &lt;code&gt;lervag/vimtex&lt;/code&gt; as a plugin while disabling lazy loading.&#xA;It is mentioned in the &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/lervag/vimtex&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;VimTex README&lt;span style=&#34;white-space: nowrap;&#34;&gt;&amp;thinsp;↗&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; lazy loading messes the &lt;code&gt;VimtexInverseSearch&lt;/code&gt; command; I tried, it really does.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>LaTeX setup for writing a paper review response</title>
      <link>https://vaclavblazej.github.io/post/2023/review_response/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 26 May 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://vaclavblazej.github.io/post/2023/review_response/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;A simple but sufficient setup to response to a review.&#xA;The &lt;code&gt;rev&lt;/code&gt; command guards that response is given and prints a red note otherwise.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;main.png&#34; alt=&#34;main.png&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;main.tex&#34;&gt;main.tex&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;background-color:#fff;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-latex&#34; data-lang=&#34;latex&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;\documentclass&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#1f2328&#34;&gt;[a4paper,USenglish]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;article&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;\usepackage&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;xcolor&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;\newcommand&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;\rev&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;[2]&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;\item&lt;/span&gt; #1 &lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;\if\relax\detokenize&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;#2&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;\relax&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;\color&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;red&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;UNANSWERED&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;\else&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;\color&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;blue&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;#2&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;\fi&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;\begin&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;document&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;\section*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;Response&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;We thank the reviewers for their reviews &lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;\dots&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;\subsection*&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;Reviewer 1&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;\begin&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;enumerate&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;\rev&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;Line 128: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;\dots&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;}{}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;\rev&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;Line 256: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;\dots&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;}{&lt;/span&gt;we changed this&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;\end&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;enumerate&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#cf222e&#34;&gt;\end&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;document&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6639ba&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>NeoVim Setup</title>
      <link>https://vaclavblazej.github.io/post/2023/neovim/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 30 Apr 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://vaclavblazej.github.io/post/2023/neovim/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Doing all my editing in Vim I thought for some time whether to switch to &lt;a href=&#34;https://neovim.io/&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;NeoVim&lt;span style=&#34;white-space: nowrap;&#34;&gt;&amp;thinsp;↗&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&#xA;A few days ago I finally decided to do the switch.&#xA;The result is &lt;strong&gt;awesome&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I ought to credit ThePrimeagen whose &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=w7i4amO_zaE&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;videotutorial&lt;span style=&#34;white-space: nowrap;&#34;&gt;&amp;thinsp;↗&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; stands was the main reason for my transition.&#xA;Another reason was a nice tutorial for using &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ejmastnak.com/tutorials/vim-latex/intro/&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;VimTeX by ejmastnak&lt;span style=&#34;white-space: nowrap;&#34;&gt;&amp;thinsp;↗&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;why&#34;&gt;Why&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Here are my reasons to use NeoVim.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;highlighting (via &lt;a href=&#34;nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter&#34;&gt;incremental syntax tree&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;support for custom &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/L3MON4D3/LuaSnip&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;code snippets&lt;span style=&#34;white-space: nowrap;&#34;&gt;&amp;thinsp;↗&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;revert local changes via &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/mbbill/undotree&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;undotree&lt;span style=&#34;white-space: nowrap;&#34;&gt;&amp;thinsp;↗&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;good support for &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/lervag/vimtex&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;LaTex&lt;span style=&#34;white-space: nowrap;&#34;&gt;&amp;thinsp;↗&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/tpope/vim-fugitive&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Git&lt;span style=&#34;white-space: nowrap;&#34;&gt;&amp;thinsp;↗&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;quick fuzzy search for files or contents &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/nvim-telescope/telescope.nvim&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;navigation&lt;span style=&#34;white-space: nowrap;&#34;&gt;&amp;thinsp;↗&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/VonHeikemen/lsp-zero.nvim&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;LSP support&lt;span style=&#34;white-space: nowrap;&#34;&gt;&amp;thinsp;↗&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;:checkhealth&lt;/code&gt; tells you what is wrong (missing dependencies, old versions, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;installation&#34;&gt;Installation&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;My current setup is available at &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/vaclavblazej/nvim&#34;target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;https://github.com/vaclavblazej/nvim&lt;span style=&#34;white-space: nowrap;&#34;&gt;&amp;thinsp;↗&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&#xA;Installation on Ubuntu goes like this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Modelling problems with SAT</title>
      <link>https://vaclavblazej.github.io/post/2023/sat/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 21 Feb 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://vaclavblazej.github.io/post/2023/sat/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;We shall go through many example problems that demonstrate how to model them using Satisfiability problem.&#xA;Such model is useful because there are many fast solvers for SAT so we can use them to solve our instance and extract the solution back to our original problem.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;We aim to create a formula in Conjunctive Normal Form (CNF):&#xA;$$(a \lor b) \land (c \lor d \lor e) \land \dots \land (f \lor g)$$&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Jak na pointery?!</title>
      <link>https://vaclavblazej.github.io/post/2023/pointers/</link>
